column5: Was out today with a few friends. Meegs got his first ever Musky and so did Slyatv. WTG guys!
NICE CATCH GUYS !!!!!!! 2 big skis,in the same day.  ..right on...cheers
Great job out there!  Awesome looking fish!  Strange looking water there...were you near a nuke plant?? LOL.
Nice pair of skis boys .Ya like Cliff says were you near a nuclear plant or did you all puke in the Lake   MTP
couple nice fish,congrats
WTG Bud. I'll betcha I know when they hit and how you got them . :-)
SaWEET!  Congrats on the firsts guys!! You set the bar high for the next ones!  Sinker
Awesome fish Guys!!  WTG!!  Very nice markings on the second one.  Bill
beauty fish GB!
Congrats on the two nice fish. That's the worst algae bloom I've ever seen
Nice job Andy!!
Very nice!  maureen

Exellent Gb...and a big congrats....you'll be hooked now! BTW, 'ReelBuddies'...that dude is Shane....awesome straight shooting stand-up person and a great friend of mine....his knowledge of Simcoe is best by far....tell him I send along a big hello howdy.
What an adrenaline rush for those two guys.  Congrats on a couple very respectable skis.

WOW! Are those Georgian bay Musky? I have never targetted Georgian bay musky but I hear it is a difficult task. Wanna give it a try.Can you at least point me in the right direction? Near Honey harbour, Parry Sound, or more north? You can email me if you like.
Nice skies! Likes like Georgian Bay has quite the algae bloom.
wow nice fish

Jeeeez Andy, I thought all anybody ever caught in your boat was weed wrapped snot rocket pike, at least when I'm with you anyways   ..... JK Bud !!  Couple beauty fish there boyz, congrats on a great day !!  BTW Andy, I thought you were coming to my place last month, wazzup ??  ....gimme a call
Nice!

Was a long time in the planning and Im glad I could produce. Both guys are good people and they were well deserved for sure. Its not the first time I've caught 2 but the way I fished them was a first for me as well. (Thanks Marc)
Real nice job on getting him his first Andy.
